    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414950>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–4. Specimens of three Castniidae collected in Mexico: 1) Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb., male, Tequila, Jalisco, ex-larva in Agave tequilana Weber var.Azul (photo: Jorge Valdez Carrasco); 2) E. chelone (Hopffer) n. comb., male, Ixmiquilpan, Hidalgo (photo: Adolfo Ibarra); 3) E. estherae (J.Y. Miller) n. comb., female, Zoyatepec, Guerrero (photo: Bernardo López G.); 4) E. estherae (J.Y. Miller), male, Zoyatepec, Guerrero (photo: Bernardo López G.)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414950/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414960>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb. legs: (a) foreleg; (b) midleg; (c) hindleg." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414960/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414962>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb. male palpus and male wing venation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414962/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414954>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–8. Male genitalia (lateral view) of three species of Castniidae: 6) Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb., (genitalia preparation M-2543, Jacqueline Y. Miller), Paratype, Acahuizotla, Guerrero, Mexico; viii.1973. Coll. A. Diaz Francis.; 7) E. chelone (Hopffer) n. comb. (from Miller (1976) Bull. Allyn Mus. 34: 1–13); 8) E. estherae (J.Y. Miller) n. comb. (genitalia preparation, Fernando Hernández-Baz), Zoyatepec, Guerrero, Mexico, iv.6.2016, Coll. J. P. Huerta P. (a) genital capsule; (b) phallus (phallobase + aedeagus); (c) uncus, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414954/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414956>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb., posterior view of uncus and tegumen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414956/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414964>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Escalantiana escalantei (J.Y. Miller) n. comb., female genitalia (dorsal Slide M-3028, Jacqueline Y. Miller) Mexico: Guerrero: Acahuizotla; v. 1958; Tarcisio Escalante." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414964/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3414968>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Habitat in which Escalantiana estherae (J.Y. Miller) n. comb. was collected in Zoyatepec, Guerrero, Mexico: a) access to site showing bushes and some of the tree species; b) Tropical Deciduous Forest with oaks with multiple epiphytic plants; c) Tillandsia prodigiosa (Lemaire) Baker (Bromeliaceae) plants on branches of an oak (Quercus sp., Fagaceae). (Photos: John Phill Huerta P.)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3414968/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

